The paper deals with the problem of mobile robot map building, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The approach presented in the paper involves modeling the structure of a typical environment using a hidden Markov model, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Dirichlet priors and hyperparameters, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The experiments involve processing robot data, which may involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of multi-robot map merging, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
